HEADWORD: Cole
<hw>Cole</hw> <pr>(k⟦omac⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>col</ets>, <ets>caul</ets>, AS. <ets>cawl</ets>, <ets>cawel</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>caulis</ets>, the stalk or stem of a plant, esp. a cabbage
stalk, cabbage, akin to Gr. <grk>kaylo`s</grk>. Cf.
<er>Cauliflower</er>, <er>Kale</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
plant of the <gen>Brassica</gen> or Cabbage genus; esp. that form of
<spn>Brassica oleracea</spn> called <altname>rape</altname> and
<altname>coleseed</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

